{"updated_at": "2012-08-23T13:43:46Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2012-08-23T13:43:46Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/7969895", "id": 7969895, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/7400", "issue_id": 7400, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/repos", "type": "User", "html_url": "https://github.com/bogdan", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "91913f6ab8085bab0f2aa43995ba8ca2", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/91913f6ab8085bab0f2aa43995ba8ca2?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F926d19e70f74c20f796d376aafa3c6e2.png", "id": 122436, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/events{/privacy}", "login": "bogdan", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bogdan/followers"}, "body": "Comming back to my original use case: factory like method that ends with `save!`:\nUsing `tap &:save!` solves the problem, but imho makes it a little dirty - minor issue but fix is just one line of code.\n\nI don't see any evil and backward compatibility problems in this patch.\nThe code that relay on `true` as return value would look like:\n\n``` ruby\nif object.save! == true\n```\n\nThis is very likely not going to happen because includes two mistakes in a row.\nAnd as I said returning `self` may be useful. Returning `true` will never be useful.", "_id": {"$oid": "5237fc05bd3543c15100b8ba"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7400#issuecomment-7969895"}
